Daily Electricity Price and Demand Estimation¶

By Jesse Saechao¶

Purpose¶

The main goal of this project is to utilize demand estimation techniques with electricity demand data from a PJM energy consumption data set, https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/robikscube/hourly-energy-consumption.

Data Cleaning¶

Data was cleaned separately using R. Each energy utility was merged and totals were calculated for overall hourly energy consumption. 2044 duplicate values were removed.

Data from 2018-08 was removed in R because of a lack of completeness in hourly data. This led to lower monthly totals which skewed the data.

Let's create daily and montly data from hourly data¶

This groupy method will group each Datetime, which is currently in hours, to Datetime in days and will sum each utility's load.

In [89]:
len(df['Datetime'].unique()), len(df['Datetime']) # Checks for consistency
df_daily = df.groupby(pd.Grouper(key = 'Datetime', axis = 0, freq='D')).sum().reset_index()
df_monthly = df.groupby(pd.Grouper(key = 'Datetime', axis = 0 ,freq = 'M')).sum().reset_index()

Stationarity Testing¶

It's obvious that there'a seasonal component to this time series. Nonetheless, here are the dickey-fuller results from testing for stationarity.

Stationarity testing was performed on daily data, subsetted in years. This helps significantly in identifying stationarity.

In [93]:
st_1718 = adfuller(df_1718.totals, regression = 'ct', autolag = 'AIC')
print("P-value: ", st_1718[1])
 
#pacf = plot_pacf(df.totals, method='ywm', lags = 12)

P-value:  0.14117427849177377

The p-value is greater than 0.05 which implies that autocorrelation is at play here and the data is not stationary. A potential solution to this is first differencing.

In [94]:
df_1718['firstdiff'] = df_1718.totals - df_1718.totals.shift(1)
first_df = df_1718.dropna().reset_index()
first_df = first_df[['Datetime', 'firstdiff']]

st_firstdiff = adfuller(first_df.firstdiff, regression = 'ct', autolag = 'AIC')
print("P-value: ", st_firstdiff[1])

  df_1718['firstdiff'] = df_1718.totals - df_1718.totals.shift(1)

After performing a first-difference, the p-value vastly improves and the data is now consistent.
